3 columns of 100px 
grid-template-columns: 100px 100px 100px 


grid-template-columns: auto 50px 10% 2fr 1fr; 

unit fr puts rows and columns to fraction of available space 
auto: puts it in size of space
and here 50px means it will stay 50px no matter how you stretch the page 
10% is 10% of the whole container
2fr and 1fr, so this means 2 sections to 1 column which is 4 and 1 to fifth  




2 rows of 50px high 
grid-template-rows:50px 50px  


grid-column-gap: 20px; between columns 

grid-row-gap: 10px; between rows 


grid-gap:10px 20px; 

first is for rows, second is for columns 


grid-column: 2/4
grid-rows: 2/4
take multiple rows and columns 


repeat function repeats things multiple times 


grid-template-rows: repeat(2,1fr 50px) 20px 

first number of times we wnat it to repeat 

how the above is calculated:
grid-template-rows: 1fr 50px 1fr 50px 20px 



gird-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr)


min-max function 


first is the smallest size a row or column could be and the second is the largest a row or column colud be 

grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(90px, 1fr))



